But arrival rebuilds terrain/environment:
- Server `CmdStartScene` calls `GameNetwork::startScene()` at [GameNetwork.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/network/GameNetwork.cpp:630).
- `startScene()` deletes old `GroundScene`, then calls `Game::setScene(...)` at [GameNetwork.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/network/GameNetwork.cpp:480).
- `GroundScene::load()` creates a new `TerrainObject` and new terrain appearance at [GroundScene.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/scene/GroundScene.cpp:1313).
- `ClientSpaceTerrainAppearance` constructs a fresh `SpaceEnvironment` at [ClientSpaceTerrainAppearance.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientTerrain/src/shared/appearance/ClientSpaceTerrainAppearance.cpp:24).
- Fresh distant planets are pushed active by default into `m_objectsToDisableForHyperspace` at [SpaceEnvironment.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientTerrain/src/shared/appearance/SpaceEnvironment.cpp:196).

Destination “leave hyperspace” does **not** disable them:
- After loading, `GroundScene` creates `HyperspaceIoWin(..., S_leave)` only if the prior enter flag was set: [GroundScene.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/scene/GroundScene.cpp:2113).
- `S_leave` queues `CockpitLeaveStage` only: [HyperspaceIoWin.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/HyperspaceIoWin.cpp:966).
- `CockpitLeaveStage::hideOtherObjects()` returns false, so `CockpitStage::draw()` skips the disable path: [HyperspaceIoWin.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/HyperspaceIoWin.cpp:730).

(b) **Station launch is not affected by this disable path in the operator case.** Launch UI sends `launchIntoSpace` ([SwgCuiShipView.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/game/client/library/swgClientUserInterface/src/shared/page/SwgCuiShipView.cpp:268)); actual zone entry is server `CmdStartScene` -> new `GroundScene`/new space terrain. If `CM_aboutToHyperspace` fires while still on ground, `deactivateSpaceEnvironmentObjects()` dynamic-casts the terrain appearance to `ClientSpaceTerrainAppearance` and no-ops on ground terrain: [HyperspaceIoWin.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/HyperspaceIoWin.cpp:323).

(c) **Stock/fork status:** `SpaceEnvironment.cpp` and `HyperspaceIoWin.cpp` are stock-import files here. `git log --follow` shows only `37ab0ad07 initial commit`; `git diff` is empty; headers retain SOE 2004 copyright at [SpaceEnvironment.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientTerrain/src/shared/appearance/SpaceEnvironment.cpp:3) and [HyperspaceIoWin.cpp](/D:/Code/swg-client-v2/src/engine/client/library/clientGame/src/shared/core/HyperspaceIoWin.cpp:2).

**Bottom line:** do **not** fix this by adding `setActive(true)` for the reported station-launch empty-space issue. The no-reactivation claim is only locally true inside one `SpaceEnvironment`; zone arrival recreates it. If you still want a defensive fix for same-scene/cancelled hyperspace, add `SpaceEnvironment::enableEnvironmentForHyperspace()` and call it from `CockpitStage::finish()` only when that stage disabled objects. But for this symptom, this is **not the bug**.
